Linux CLI Basic :-

        Basic Commands :-
                         * pwd :
                                Print working directory
                         * ls /dir:
                               List of Folder.
                         * tree :
                                 To see tree of folders.
                         * ls -la :
                                   List of hidden file in detail.
                         * cd < Folder name > :
                                             Change directory.
                         * cd .. :
                                  To move one director back.
                         * cd ~ :
                                 To move to home location.
                         * cd / :
                                 To move to root location .
                         * cat < file.txt > :
                                            To read a file.
                         * touch < file.txt > :
                                             To create an empty file.
 VIP                     * nano < file.txt > :
                                             To edit a file.
                         * gedit < file.txt > :
                                              To edit a file.
                         * less :
                                 To see short of content in a  long file .
                         * head :
                                To see top of content in a long file.
                         * tail :
                                 To see bottom of content of long file.
                         * ./ :
                               To execute a shell file.
                         * wc -l :
                                  To count number of line of file.
                         * cp <file> Location :
                                               To copy a file
                         * cp -r :
                                  To copy directory
                         * rm :
                               To remove file or directory.
                         * rm <file.txt> :
                                               To remove a file.
                         * grep word <file.txt> :
                                                 To Find a word from 1000 of words in file like password.
                         * mkdir :
                                    To create a directory.
                         * rmdir :
                                    To remove a directory.
                         * sudo su :
                                    To take root permission.
                         * Chmod +x < File.txt > :
                                                  To give execution control to a file.
                         * history :
                                   To see history of commands
                         * clear :
                                  To clear terminal.
                         * man < command > :
                                            To see manual or detail of a command.
                         * < command > --help :
                                             To see help about command.
                         * What is < command > :
                                                To see short intro of command.
                         * who is < google.com > :
                                                  To see full detail of any domain.
                         * df -h :
                                  Hard disk report .
                         * free -h :
                                    RAM health report.
                         * uname -a :
                                    System version detail.
                         * ping < google.com > :
                                                speed of packet sending and response.
                         * traceroute < google.com > :
                                                      packet send rout info
                         * netstat :
                                   To check which port is open.
                         * dig < google.com > :
                                              To check ip of domain.
                         * nslookup < google.com > :
                                                    To check domain and ip of web in fast way.
                         * whois < google.com > :
                                                To see max detail of web.
                         * Ctrl + Z :
                                     To pause a command in terminal .
                         * fg :
                                 To resume pause command on foreground

